<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Pearson Quarks</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/styles/style.css">
    <script type="text/javascript" src="./quarks-visualisation.js"></script>
    <%= livereload %>
</head>
<body onload="init()">
<div class="page">
    <header>
        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Horizontal_Blk_RGB.svg" alt="Pearson logo">
        <div class="menu">
            <nav>
                <a href="#logo">
                    Logo
                </a>
                <a href="#color">
                    Color
                </a>
                <a href="#typography">
                    Typography
                </a>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </header>
    <div class="main">
        <!---->
        <div class="content">
            <article id="welcome">
                <div class="avatar">
                    <canvas id="canvasOne" width="280" height="280" ></canvas>
                </div>

                <div class="claim">
                    <h1>Pearson Quarks</h1>
                    <h2>Pearson brand assets for software development</h2>
                </div>

                <div class="benefits">
                    <section>
                        <h2>Quick project bootsraping</h2>
                        <p>
                            Get all brand resources you need on start of digital products development and save your time for searching and writing simple code.
                        </p>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <h2>Technology Independent</h2>
                        <p>
                            Use with web and native apps. Color palettes and mixins are available in LESS, SASS, Stylus, and XML. Quarks don’t depend on any libraries or frameworks.    
                        </p>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <h2>Simple & flexible</h2>
                        <p>
                            Get visuals assets from CDN or download them and host by yourself. Don’t waste your time for graphics and font format conversion.   
                        </p>
                    </section>
                </div>
            </article>
            <article class="gray-bg logo-section">
                <h1 id="logo">Logo</h1>
                <p>The primary version of our logo should be used wherever possible. Where the primary version is not
                appropriate, e.g, in digital environments or where there is restrictive space, we also have a horizontal
                version.</p>

                <h2>Primary Logo</h2>

                <div class="griddy">
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal Mono White">
                            </div>
                        <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Primary Black</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Mono_Blk_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal Mono White">
                            </div>
                        <div class="card-content">   
                        <h3>Primary Mono Black</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container dark">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_W_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal Mono White">
                            </div>
                        <div class="card-content">    
                            <h3>Primary White</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container dark">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Mono_W_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal Mono White">
                            </div>
                        <div class="card-content">   
                        <h3>Primary Mono White</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                </div>

                <h2>Horizontal Logo</h2>

                <div class="griddy">
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Horizontal_Blk_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal">
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Horizontal Black</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                   
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Horizontal_Mono_Blk_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal Mono">
                            </div>
                        <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Horizontal Black Mono</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container dark">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Horizontal_Mono_W_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal Mono White">
                            </div>
                        <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Horizontal White Mono</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <div class="logo-container dark">
                        <img src="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Horizontal_W_RGB.svg" alt="Logo Horizontal White">
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Horizontal White</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-actions">
                            <a href="assets/images/logos/PearsonLogo_Primary_Blk_RGB.svg">SVG</a>
                            <a href="#logo">PNG</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>
               
                </div>
            </article>
            <article class="color-section">
                <h1 id="color">Color</h1>
                <p>
                Color brings a design to life. Color is versatile; it's used to express emotion and tone, as well as
                place emphasis and create associations. Color should always be used in meaningful and intentional ways
                in order to create patterns and visual cues.</p>

                {{#each palettes}}
                <section>
                    <h2>{{this.name}}</h2>

                    <ul class="color-list griddy">
                    {{#each colors}}
                    <li>
                        <div class="color-marker color-{{@key}}">

                        </div>
                        <h3>{{this.name}}</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>{{this.hex}}</li>
                            <li>$pc-color-{{@key}}</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    {{/each}}
                    </ul>
                </section>
                {{/each}}
            </article>
            <article id="typography" class="typo-section">
                <h1 id="typography">Typography</h1>
                <p>
                Our brand typefaces are Playfair Display and Open Sans. Using both serif and sans serif typefaces gives
                us the flexibility to cover our wide range of audiences and communications.</p>
                <section class="font-box">
                    <div class="playfair-typo-demo">
                        Playfair display
                    </div>

                    <p>
                    Use for headings in marketing material and simple webistes
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        $pc__titles--font-family
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="font-box">
                    <div class="open-sans-typo-demo">
                        Open Sans
                    </div>

                    <p>
                    Use for for body and and headings in apps
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        $pc--font-family
                    </p>
                </section>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
<script>
  function init() {

    canvasApp();

  }
</script>
</html>